# 1. Time Complexity

### Definition

Time Complexity measures how the execution time grows as input size increases.

### Common Complexities

| Complexity | Name         |
| ---------- | ------------ |
| O(1)       | Constant     |
| O(log n)   | Logarithmic  |
| O(n)       | Linear       |
| O(n log n) | Linearithmic |
| O(n²)      | Quadratic    |
| O(2ⁿ)      | Exponential  |
| O(n!)      | Factorial    |

### Example O(1)

```java
int x = arr[0];
```

### Example O(n)

```java
for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
{
    System.out.println(i);
}
```

### Example O(n²)

```java
for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
{
    for(int j=0;j<n;j++)
    {
        System.out.println(i+" "+j);
    }
}
```

